    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Edible rounded bulbs of Allium cepa, which consist of fleshy concentric leaf-bases. Onions have a strong pungent flavour and smell, and vary in color from white to yellow and dark red, and are used as a culinary vegetable throughout the world, eaten raw, cooked, or pickled.</Note_Text>
